tafsir[3]{c,v,t}:
  71,19,"And Allah hath made the earth a wide expanse for you) to lay and sleep on"
  71,20,"(That ye may thread the valley ways thereof) that you may follow wide ways thereof."
  71,21,"(Noah said: My Lord!) O my Lord! (They have disobeyed me) regarding repentance and faith in Allah's divine Oneness (and followed) and obeyed (one whose) abundant (wealth and children increase him in naught save ruin) in the Hereafter; this refers to the chieftains of his folk;"